gomodel:SYNGO_4136  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Fig3 A-B: Both SNX16 and SNX16-GFP localized to several bright puncta in each synaptic bouton, which overlapped well with the early endosomal markers Rab5 and Rab4.\nFig3F: Immunoelectron microscopy with anti-GFP antibodies detected both SNX16-GFP and SNX16-GFP on early endosome and multivesicular like structures in the NMJ.\nFig S2: GFP and Snx16 in UAS-Snx16-GFP lines showed colocalisation indicating that the GFP antibody used for the localisation experiment are representative of snx16.. Experimental description: UAS-Snx16 and UAS-Snx16-GFP lines were constructed in pUAST (Brand and Perrimon, 1993) carrying the Snx16 cDNA (clone SD19533; Berkeley Drosophila Genome Project)." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-2916-7616" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" ;
        dc:date           "2021-01-18" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_4136" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_7227" .

